<h1>Using native events with the on helper</h1>

<p>Syntax: <code>&lt;Input &#123;&#123;on "event" this.someAction&#125;&#125; /&gt;</code></p>

<h2>👍 Yes:</h2>
<ol>
  <li>
    <label for="keyup">Event is keyup</label>
    <Input {{on "keyup" this.updateName}} id="keyup"/>
  </li>
</ol>

<h2>👎 No:</h2>
<ol>
  <li>
    <label for="key-up">Event is key-up</label>
    <Input {{on "key-up" this.updateName}} id="key-up" />

  </li>
</ol>